Creates a new Amazon Chime SDK meeting in the specified media Region with no initial attendees

Source: R/chime_operations.R
chime_create_meeting.Rd

Creates a new Amazon Chime SDK meeting in the specified media Region with no initial attendees. For more information about specifying media Regions, see Amazon Chime SDK Media Regions in the Amazon Chime Developer Guide. For more information about the Amazon Chime SDK, see Using the Amazon Chime SDK in the Amazon Chime Developer Guide.

chime_create_meeting(ClientRequestToken, ExternalMeetingId,
  MeetingHostId, MediaRegion, Tags, NotificationsConfiguration)

Arguments

ClientRequestToken

[required] The unique identifier for the client request. Use a different token for different meetings.
ExternalMeetingId

The external meeting ID.
MeetingHostId

Reserved.
MediaRegion

The Region in which to create the meeting. Default: us-east-1.

Available values: ap-northeast-1, ap-southeast-1, ap-southeast-2, ca-central-1, eu-central-1, eu-north-1, eu-west-1, eu-west-2, eu-west-3, sa-east-1, us-east-1, us-east-2, us-west-1, us-west-2.
Tags

The tag key-value pairs.
NotificationsConfiguration

The configuration for resource targets to receive notifications when meeting and attendee events occur.

Request syntax

svc$create_meeting(
  ClientRequestToken = "string",
  ExternalMeetingId = "string",
  MeetingHostId = "string",
  MediaRegion = "string",
  Tags = list(
    list(
      Key = "string",
      Value = "string"
    )
  ),
  NotificationsConfiguration = list(
    SnsTopicArn = "string",
    SqsQueueArn = "string"
  )
)
